replies.text:
@ThinkingandTinkering I would say human beings are an irrational species and awful when it comes to risk assessment. Americans are almost certain to rub out their eyes with a toothbrush unless it carries a warning label. The short answer is lawsuits.  For instance, the worry of a lawsuit is enough to stop me from turning the downstairs neighbor's unit into one of your 500 degree sand batteries.
I read up on the risks on 3d printers, the science certainly implies put it a box and send the fumes out the window. It adds a bit to the cost, but it depends on how you price things.   By operating my battery as a Interruptible Power supply - meaning I cut it off from the grid intentionally during peak hours, the battery, the printer, and the box, will pay for themselves in about two years. 
I find you quite inspiring and you made at least one Elegoo sale and a no-fault Fungoo sale because Elegoo doesn't make a box for the Plus. I'm leaving for another camping trip early next week, so no builds until I return I'm afraid. I had decided on my first build of yours and how to go about it, fire up the printer, get on the rower,  put on the headphones, and listen to a favorite album of mine since I was 10 or 11, John Barleycorn  Must Die...but it looks like you pulled the files on that one.  As always, cheers.

@oildalestar I disagree with you, I mean absolutely no disrespect, and would like to explain that I'm "Underclass" where finances are concerned.
However, I will be saving up in order to buy myself a 3D printer for Xmas!!
You are absolutely  right about Taxes mind you, and since I  don't agree with  how those taxes are spent, I'm working on little projects, rather than paying for  politicians yatchs,Etc..
